## What Was Fixed ✅

### 1. Test Project Added
A `DiskCloner.UnitTests` project was created with xUnit and 3 tests covering hashing and sector-aligned padding via [TestHelpers.cs](file:///Users/pisarz/Documents/projekty/test-diskcloning/DiskCloner.Core/Utilities/TestHelpers.cs). This is a solid start.

### 2. `bin/obj` Removed from Git
Confirmed 0 build artifacts are tracked — the [.gitignore](file:///Users/pisarz/Documents/projekty/test-diskcloning/.gitignore) is now effective.

### 3. SHA-256 Reuse Bug Fixed
Source and target now use **independent** `SHA256` instances (`srcSha` / `tgtSha`) in both full and sample verification paths. Correct.

### 4. Sector-Aligned Write Padding
New `TestHelpers.GetSectorPaddedBuffer()` utility ensures writes are sector-aligned with proper zero-padding. Unit tested.

### 5. Improved Diskpart Scripting
- Recovery partitions now get correct GPT type ID and attributes
- Disk is taken offline before raw writes (critical for Windows)
- [OnlineTargetDiskAsync()](file:///Users/pisarz/Documents/projekty/test-diskcloning/DiskCloner.Core/Services/DiskClonerEngine.cs#1714-1768) brings disk back after copy
- Better error handling for access-denied during pre-clear

### 6. Partition Offset Mapping
New [ApplyTargetPartitionOffsets()](file:///Users/pisarz/Documents/projekty/test-diskcloning/DiskCloner.Core/Services/DiskClonerEngine.cs#584-638) maps source partition offsets to actual target offsets from diskpart output, preventing mis-aligned writes. Safety checks abort on mismatch.

---

## New Issues Found on This Branch 🆕

### 17. `DiskCloner.UnitTests` Not in Solution File

The [.sln](file:///Users/pisarz/Documents/projekty/test-diskcloning/DiskCloner.sln) has `DiskCloner.Tests` but **not** `DiskCloner.UnitTests`. Running `dotnet test DiskCloner.sln` will miss the new unit tests.

```
# In DiskCloner.sln — present:
Project("...") = "DiskCloner.Tests" ...
# Missing:
# Project("...") = "DiskCloner.UnitTests" ...
```

### 18. [TestHelpers](file:///Users/pisarz/Documents/projekty/test-diskcloning/DiskCloner.Core/Utilities/TestHelpers.cs#11-42) Lives in Production Assembly

[TestHelpers.cs](file:///Users/pisarz/Documents/projekty/test-diskcloning/DiskCloner.Core/Utilities/TestHelpers.cs) is in `DiskCloner.Core` — the production library. Test-only utilities should live in the test project or use `[InternalsVisibleTo]` if they need access to internals.

### 19. Loose [wmi_test.cs](file:///Users/pisarz/Documents/projekty/test-diskcloning/wmi_test.cs) in Project Root

A stray [wmi_test.cs](file:///Users/pisarz/Documents/projekty/test-diskcloning/wmi_test.cs) file sits in the repo root — not part of any project. Should be deleted or moved into the test project.

